,'inherit','closed','closed','','ufcw-anatomy-of-an-union-card','','','2017-01-05 12:23:02','2017-01-05 17:23:02','',125,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/UFCW-Anatomy-of-an-Union-Card.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(133,3,'2017-01-05 20:55:04','2017-01-06 01:55:04',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','133','','','2017-01-17 18:11:40','2017-01-17 23:11:40','',0,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/?p=133',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(134,3,'2017-01-05 20:55:04','2017-01-06 01:55:04','','Inside the UFCW','','publish','closed','closed','','134','','','2017-01-17 18:11:40','2017-01-17 23:11:40','',0,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/?p=134',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(137,2,'2017-01-12 01:38:47','2017-01-12 06:38:47','Union organizers may approach you at work, at your home, during informational meetings or through social media to ask you to sign a union card or petition.\r\n\r\nBefore you decide, be sure to ask and get answers from union organizers to all of your questions, including the following questions, so you can make a fully informed choice:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong> Will the union guarantee in writing that I will get higher wages?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Can the union force BayCare to change its health insurance program?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Is it possible that in the union’s bargaining with BayCare I could lose things I have?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Can the union get BayCare to change or fire my manager or supervisor?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Can the union guarantee that I will get the hours or schedule that I want?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"6\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Exactly how much will my monthly dues be?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"7\">\r\n 	<li><strong> How often will the union raise the amount of dues I have to pay?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"8\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Can the union take money (other than dues) out of my paycheck?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"9\">\r\n 	<li><strong> If the union wins the right to represent me, will I be pressured to pay union dues if I choose not to?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"10\">\r\n 	<li><strong> If the union is voted in at BayCare, how long will it be before we have our first signed contract? Is there any time limit for how long it can take?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"11\">\r\n 	<li><strong> If the union calls a strike, how much money can I expect to receive from the union? </strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"12\">\r\n 	<li><strong> If the union decides to strike, will the union pay my bills while I’m out of work or get me another job if I’m permanently replaced?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"13\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Will the union provide us with a copy of its constitution and bylaws before I decide whether or not to sign a union authorization card? </strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"14\">\r\n 	<li><strong> What percentage of my dues will the union actually spend addressing my workplace? </strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"15\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Will the union guarantee in writing any of the promises or implied promises it’s making? </strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','15 Questions to Ask Union Organizers','','publish','closed','closed','','15-questions-to-ask-union-organizers','','','2017-01-17 19:06:38','2017-01-18 00:06:38','',0,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/?p=137',0,'post','',0),(138,2,'2017-01-12 01:39:30','2017-01-12 06:39:30','','15-questions-to-ask-a-union-organizer','','inherit','closed','closed','','15-questions-to-ask-a-union-organizer','','','2017-01-12 01:39:30','2017-01-12 06:39:30','',137,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/15-Questions-to-Ask-a-Union-Organizer.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(139,2,'2017-01-12 01:43:37','2017-01-12 06:43:37','Union organizers may approach you at work, at your home, during informational meetings or through social media to ask you to sign a union card or petition.\n\nBefore you decide, be sure to ask and get answers from union organizers to all of your questions, including the following questions, so you can make a fully informed choice:\n<ol>\n 	<li><strong> Will the union guarantee in writing that I will get higher wages?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"2\">\n 	<li><strong> Can the union force BayCare to change its health insurance program?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"3\">\n 	<li><strong> Is it possible that in the union’s bargaining with BayCare I could lose things I have?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"4\">\n 	<li><strong> Can the union get BayCare to change or fire my manager or supervisor?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"5\">\n 	<li><strong> Can the union guarantee that I will get the hours or schedule that I want?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"6\">\n 	<li><strong> Exactly how much will my monthly dues be?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"7\">\n 	<li><strong> How often will the union raise the amount of dues I have to pay?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"8\">\n 	<li><strong> Can the union take money (other than dues) out of my paycheck?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"9\">\n 	<li><strong> If the union wins the right to represent me, will I be pressured to pay union dues if I choose not to?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"10\">\n 	<li><strong> If the union is voted in at BayCare, how long will it be before we have our first signed contract? Is there any time limit for how long it can take?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n<ol start=\"11\">\n 	<li><strong> If the union calls a strike, how much money can I expect to receive from the union? </strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n<ol start=\"12\">\n 	<li><strong> If the union decides to strike, will the union pay my bills while I’m out of work or get me another job if I’m permanently replaced?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n<ol start=\"13\">\n 	<li><strong> Will the union provide us with a copy of its constitution and bylaws before I decide whether or not to sign a union authorization card? </strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n<ol start=\"14\">\n 	<li><strong> What percentage of my dues will the union actually spend addressing my workplace? </strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n<ol start=\"15\">\n 	<li><strong> Will the union guarantee in writing any of the promises or implied promises it’s making? </strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnion’s Answer ________________________________________________________________\n\n&nbsp;','15 Questions to Ask Union Organizers','','inherit','closed','closed','','137-autosave-v1','','','2017-01-12 01:43:37','2017-01-12 06:43:37','',137,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/137-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(140,2,'2017-01-12 02:28:13','2017-01-12 07:28:13','Do you want the union and co-workers to have your personal information?\r\n\r\nJust by signing a union authorization card or petition, the union and its supporters will have access to a lot of personal information about you – information you may think should be personal and private.\r\n\r\nIf the union becomes your representative, it may have even more information about you, including your:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Name</li>\r\n 	<li>Home address</li>\r\n 	<li>Social Security Number</li>\r\n 	<li>Signature</li>\r\n 	<li>Wage rate</li>\r\n 	<li>Access to your confidential human resources file, including your health and retirement benefit information</li>\r\n 	<li>Personal e-mail</li>\r\n 	<li>Personal phone numbers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Keep your personal information private,\r\ndon’t sign a union card or petition.</h2>','Protect Your Privacy','','publish','closed','closed','','protect-your-privacy','','','2017-01-17 22:59:20','2017-01-18 03:59:20','',0,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/?p=140',0,'post','',0),(141,2,'2017-01-12 02:27:32','2017-01-12 07:27:32','','protect-your-privacy','','inherit','closed','closed','','protect-your-privacy','','','2017-01-12 02:27:32','2017-01-12 07:27:32','',140,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Protect-Your-Privacy.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(143,2,'2017-01-12 02:30:30','2017-01-12 07:30:30','','Facts About SEIU','','publish','closed','closed','','143','','','2017-01-18 14:28:10','2017-01-18 19:28:10','',7,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/?p=143',13,'nav_menu_item','',0),(144,2,'2017-01-12 02:30:30','2017-01-12 07:30:30','','Facts About UFCW','','publish','closed','closed','','144','','','2017-01-18 14:28:10','2017-01-18 19:28:10','',8,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/?p=144',17,'nav_menu_item','',0),(145,0,'2017-01-12 18:49:32','2017-01-12 23:49:32','Hi wpengine,\n\nThis notice confirms that your password was changed on BayCare.\n\nIf you did not change your password, please contact the Site Administrator at\nadmin@rezon8.net\n\nThis email has been sent to bitbucket@wpengine.com\n\nRegards,\nAll at BayCare\nhttp://baycare.wpengine.com','[BayCare] Notice of Password Change','','private','closed','closed','','baycare-notice-of-password-change','','','2017-01-12 18:49:32','2017-01-12 23:49:32','',0,'http://baycare.wpengine.com/baycare-notice-of-password-change',0,'postman_sent_mail','',0),(146,2,'2017-01-12 19:17:17','2017-01-13 00:17:17','Content-Type: text/plain; charset = \"UTF-8\"\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit\r\n\r\nHello!\r\n\r